\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Tools to quantify ecological memory in long time-series with Random Forest
 models (Breiman 2001) fitted with the 'ranger' library (Wright and Ziegler
 2017).
 Particularly oriented to palaeoecological datasets and simulated pollen
 curves produced by the 'virtualPollen' package, but also applicable to
 other long time-series involving a set of environmental drivers and a biotic
 response.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Argument 5
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

